{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3333645,"name":"mrmatheou","username":"mrmatheou","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/e0b2c6/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-03-15T10:51:20.975Z","cooked":"<p>Hello, I’m a former <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> Team Coach / Advisor (10 years) and “retired” and am back 10 years later to help my son’s team.  We’re at competition and we’ve realized it would be great to have a button that would have the robot turn to 45 degrees or -45 degrees so it could align with a wall that is 45 degree to pick up the game piece (“note”).</p>
<p>I am the programming coach on his team and have implemented a Swerve Drive System (mki L2).</p>
<p>I’m basically checking to see if you “TurnCCW90” or “TurnCW90”  (yes we changed it to 45 as this is more useful to use but haven’t renamed variables yet) is pressed on the controller and if so, then manually send 10% power to the turning motors for 3 seconds.  I hope to eventually use the Gyro to durn exactly 45 but we’re just trying this for a test right now.  Here’s an excerpt of the code:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Blockquote</p>
</blockquote>
<p>if (fieldOrientedFunction.get() &amp;&amp; !TurnCCW90 &amp;&amp; !TurnCW90)<br>
{<br>
// Relative to field<br>
chassisSpeeds = ChassisSpeeds.fromFieldRelativeSpeeds(<br>
xSpeed, ySpeed, turningSpeed, swerveSubsystem.getRotation2d());<br>
}</p>
<pre><code>	// Turn CCW
	else if (TurnCCW90)
	{

		// To break out of command by moving either of the 3 drive axis.
        //KDM 3/15/24 5:49am:  This also means that the robot has to be stopped before the "Turn90" code will execute
        //Also, perhaps we should consider using "Fromrelative speeds" to use a Gyro differentrial and while loop to do turning instead of time?
		if (xSpeed &gt; 0.1 || xSpeed &lt; -0.1 || ySpeed &gt; 0.1 || ySpeed &lt; -0.1 || turningSpeed &gt; 0.1 || turningSpeed &lt; -0.1)
		{
			TurnCCW90 = false;
		}

		else
		{
			chassisSpeeds = new ChassisSpeeds(0.0, 0.0, -0.1);

			try
			{
				Thread.sleep(3000); // Wait 3 sec
			} 

			catch (InterruptedException e) 
			{
				e.printStackTrace();
				// handle the exception...        
				// For example consider calling Thread.currentThread().interrupt(); here.
			}

			// Turn False to end
			TurnCCW90 = false;
		}
	}

	// Turn CW
	else if (TurnCW90)
	{

		// To break out of command by moving either of the 3 drive axis.
		if (xSpeed &gt; 0.1 || xSpeed &lt; -0.1 || ySpeed &gt; 0.1 || ySpeed &lt; -0.1 || turningSpeed &gt; 0.1 || turningSpeed &lt; -0.1)
		{
			TurnCW90 = false;
		}

		else
		{
			chassisSpeeds = new ChassisSpeeds(0.0, 0.0, 0.1);

			try
			{
				Thread.sleep(3000); // Wait 3 sec
			} 

			catch (InterruptedException e) 
			{
				e.printStackTrace();
				// handle the exception...        
				// For example consider calling Thread.currentThread().interrupt(); here.
			}

			// Turn False to end
			TurnCW90 = false;
		}
	}

	else 
	{
        // Relative to robot
        chassisSpeeds = new ChassisSpeeds(xSpeed, ySpeed, turningSpeed);
    }
</code></pre>
